1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:05,360
This series is a work of fiction inspired by
questions that arise within the human heart.

2
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:09,760
It is not intended to offend or pass judgment
on any beliefs, religions, or individuals.

3
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,960
(Previous Chapter) )You're going on to
the seminary with Kongdech, right?

4
00:00:13,050 --> 00:00:14,050
Right?

5
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,120
And where did your rosary go?

6
00:00:18,770 --> 00:00:20,200
I don't know where I left it.

7
00:00:21,210 --> 00:00:22,210
I ran into Barth.

8
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:24,700
He dropped it.

9
00:00:25,060 --> 00:00:26,400
He must be suspicious about us.

10
00:00:26,670 --> 00:00:27,900
Calm down. It's nothing.

11
00:00:31,730 --> 00:00:34,300
I'm tired. And I'm scared.

12
00:00:34,730 --> 00:00:36,100
And I'm not happy at all.

13
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:38,100
I'm asking you seriously, Tanrak.

14
00:00:38,550 --> 00:00:40,200
That calling from God you hear,

15
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:41,940
is it still as loud as it used to be?

16
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,200
I'm in love even though I know it's wrong.

17
00:00:46,590 --> 00:00:48,520
If this place isn't for us,

18
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:50,240
let's run away together.

19
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:57,330
FOR HIS ANGER LASTS ONLY A MOMENT,
BUT HIS FAVOR LASTS A LIFETIME;

20
00:00:57,360 --> 00:01:01,530
WEEPING MAY STAY FOR THE NIGHT,
BUT REJOICING COMES IN THE MORNING.

21
00:01:01,550 --> 00:01:02,610
PSALM 30:5

22
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,800
Looks like the power's been cut off.

23
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:43,300
There are some candles over there,

24
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:44,380
if I remember right.

25
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,560
Try looking around.

26
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:53,400
I'll look in the kitchen.

27
00:02:58,810 --> 00:02:59,810
Found one.

28
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:23,150
What are you doing?

29
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,380
Beloved.

30
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:30,980
It's mine.

31
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:34,250
I've probably had it since I was a kid.

32
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,500
B, is this your name?

33
00:03:44,730 --> 00:03:46,040
My mom had it made.

34
00:03:49,860 --> 00:03:50,900
Beloved.

35
00:03:54,510 --> 00:03:55,510
My mom…

36
00:03:56,530 --> 00:03:58,520
has called me "beloved”
since I was little.

37
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:05,200
Put it on.

38
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,150
It looks cool.

39
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,400
I think…

40
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,200
God probably won't forgive me
anytime soon.

41
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,480
Me neither.

42
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:40,200
Hey, don't get all serious.

43
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:41,760
Hm.

44
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:45,020
Right now, if you're gonna stress
about something,

45
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:47,450
stress about having no underwear.

46
00:04:48,410 --> 00:04:49,850
You forgot to bring any, didn't you?

47
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:55,110
Here.

48
00:04:56,380 --> 00:04:57,600
Take mine for now.

49
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,440
But…

50
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:02,000
it might be a little loose on you.

51
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:04,030
Let's measure.

52
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:04,900
Hey!

53
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:08,150
Will it fit? Can you wear it?

54
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:09,380
Give it.

55
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,120
Hey, Tan, you have to measure first.

56
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:11,980
Measure what?
We have to measure.

57
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,500
How else would we know if it fits?

58
00:05:15,170 --> 00:05:16,300
How would we know?

59
00:05:16,670 --> 00:05:17,670
Don't.

60
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,060
We have to measure first.

61
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,500
How else would we know?

62
00:05:20,745 --> 00:05:22,600
Give it here. Those are mine.

63
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,640
Tan…

64
00:05:44,030 --> 00:05:45,100
right now

65
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:46,780
can we…

66
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:49,120
not think about anything else?

67
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:51,800
Let it all go for now.

68
00:05:53,970 --> 00:05:55,100
Just…

69
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:58,100
having you here with me is enough.

70
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:10,830
Well…

71
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,900
I'm here with you, aren't I?

72
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:34,800
"Ticket to Heaven"
(Episode 6)

73
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,800
Here.

74
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:44,600
Proudly presenting.

75
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,600
Whoa, Barth.

76
00:07:51,130 --> 00:07:54,300
Did you toast this bread or burn it?

77
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:58,780
This is called crispy outside,
soft on the inside.

78
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,800
Come on.

79
00:08:01,050 --> 00:08:02,600
I went out and bought it for you.

80
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:05,100
Not even a tiny thank-you?

81
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,650
Aww…

82
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:10,560
Thank youuu.
Hey.

83
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:12,900
You'll get it on me.

84
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:14,650
- Thank you.
- You'll get it on me, Tanrak.

85
00:08:14,850 --> 00:08:15,900
It'll smear.

86
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:17,430
Come on, eat.

87
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:20,830
Here.

88
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,100
Tanrak, I made this for you.

89
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:30,900
Here, I got you this too.

90
00:08:48,990 --> 00:08:50,380
Eat it before it warms up.

91
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,300
You eat this better than anyone
I've ever met.

92
00:09:15,110 --> 00:09:16,110
It's good.

93
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,500
Twice as good.

94
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,100
Here.

95
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,100
Can I have some?

96
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,900
So…

97
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:48,770
what song would Nong Tanrak like to hear?

98
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,920
I don't know.

99
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:52,190
You pick.

100
00:09:57,020 --> 00:09:59,200
Then today, DJ P'Barth…

101
00:09:59,450 --> 00:10:01,120
will play a song for Nong Tanrak.

102
00:10:02,370 --> 00:10:03,400
Just now

103
00:10:03,870 --> 00:10:06,400
what were you thinking about?

104
00:10:13,540 --> 00:10:14,540
I don't know.

105
00:10:14,850 --> 00:10:17,800
I guess I was thinking about my parents.

106
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:33,500
Then…

107
00:10:33,650 --> 00:10:35,200
should we go to your house today?

108
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:39,500
My house was sold.

109
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:44,000
But if we want to go somewhere
that'll make me miss them less,

110
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:45,900
there is one other place.

111
00:10:57,280 --> 00:11:01,520
ST. PEDRO CHURCH CEMETERY GATE

112
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:09,580
Man, we shouldn't have missed
the 1 p.m. bus.

113
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:14,630
Tanrak.

114
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,840
Are you Pracha's son, Tanrak?

115
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:20,700
Yes, I am.

116
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,500
It's me, Lek.

117
00:11:28,310 --> 00:11:29,700
I almost didn't recognize you.

118
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:30,830
Hello, Auntie Lek.
Hello.

119
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:32,400
Hello.

120
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:33,550
Hello.

121
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,300
Did you only just have time to come?

122
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:38,440
I didn't see you
at last year's cemetery blessing.

123
00:11:39,770 --> 00:11:42,700
Last year, I had to go
to military cadet camp.

124
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:44,200
So I couldn't make it.

125
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:47,410
Have you paid respects
to your parents yet?

126
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,790
Not yet.

127
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,400
The cemetery's closed now.

128
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:57,480
Are you heading back,
or coming back tomorrow?

129
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:03,500
I haven't thought that far.

130
00:12:03,930 --> 00:12:05,980
If I can't find a place to stay,

131
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:08,100
I'll probably have to come another day.

132
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:09,700
Then how about this?

133
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:11,700
Stay at my place tonight.

134
00:12:11,930 --> 00:12:13,690
I'll bring you back tomorrow morning.

135
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,140
That'd be great.

136
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,570
LEK'S LAUNDRY SERVICE

137
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:25,180
Come on in, boys.

138
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:33,400
The house is a little messy.

139
00:13:00,940 --> 00:13:01,940
That's me.

140
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:03,810
In both pictures.

141
00:13:15,580 --> 00:13:16,650
Dear Lord,

142
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:18,720
please bless us

143
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,700
and the food we are about to receive.

144
00:13:21,950 --> 00:13:23,630
In the name of the Father,

145
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:24,400
and of the Son,

146
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,720
and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

147
00:13:27,210 --> 00:13:28,900
Eat up. You're hungry, aren't you?

148
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,260
Go on.

149
00:13:32,230 --> 00:13:32,900
So…

150
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:34,780
What was Tanrak like as a kid?

151
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,740
Was he as talkative as he is now?

152
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:38,610
How young are we talking?

153
00:13:38,990 --> 00:13:41,100
I've known him
since he was in an incubator.

154
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,670
As a baby, he cried all the time.

155
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:45,400
But as he got older,

156
00:13:46,140 --> 00:13:47,140
he got quieter.

157
00:13:47,630 --> 00:13:48,810
He just hid behind his dad.

158
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:53,050
How did you know Tanrak's family?

159
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:58,200
I was friends with Tanrak's dad
since we were in secondary school.

160
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,630
We went to the same school

161
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:03,400
and became really close.

162
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,800
Oh, I remember now.

163
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,400
I have photos too.

164
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,720
Ta-da.

165
00:14:26,710 --> 00:14:29,410
Auntie Lek, did you live
in Magdalene House too?

166
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:30,670
I did.

167
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,690
We started together back in Grade 7.

168
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,560
In Grade 12,

169
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:48,300
we were still hiding under blankets
studying for exams together.

170
00:14:54,910 --> 00:15:00,500
Did the rector know
you and my dad were going to leave?

171
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:02,040
Of course.

172
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,200
Father knew everything.

173
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,700
He just chose to look the other way.

174
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:10,370
I knew I had to leave either way.

175
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:17,000
I knew I wanted to be a woman
ever since I was little.

176
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:21,100
I couldn't keep going down that path.

177
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:29,380
So…

178
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:31,700
how did you feel

179
00:15:33,130 --> 00:15:34,360
when you left?

180
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,100
Well…

181
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:38,860
I did wonder.

182
00:15:39,550 --> 00:15:42,100
I wondered if, after leaving,

183
00:15:43,310 --> 00:15:45,040
God would still love me.

184
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:47,800
But in the end, here I am.

185
00:15:50,330 --> 00:15:52,500
I can still love Him just the same.

186
00:16:00,770 --> 00:16:01,770
Eat up.

187
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:03,500
You're hungry, aren't you?

188
00:16:06,390 --> 00:16:07,700
Eat some more.

189
00:16:09,890 --> 00:16:10,890
I bet

190
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:12,800
you had

191
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:16,600
a lot of friends at Magdalene House.

192
00:16:17,490 --> 00:16:18,600
A whole gang of us.

193
00:16:20,770 --> 00:16:22,200
Know who the ringleader was?

194
00:16:23,540 --> 00:16:24,540
Your dad.

195
00:16:39,430 --> 00:16:40,600
Here you go.

196
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:44,200
Thank you, Auntie Lek.

197
00:16:45,410 --> 00:16:47,300
They've been packed away.
I hardly use them.

198
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,250
Want to make the bed now? I can help.

199
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:51,800
Oh, it's okay.

200
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,200
Barth and I can do it together.

201
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,040
Barth.

202
00:16:58,070 --> 00:16:59,980
Come help me make the bed.

203
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:11,150
This Barth…

204
00:17:12,460 --> 00:17:13,800
is he your close friend?

205
00:17:14,850 --> 00:17:15,850
Oh.

206
00:17:16,330 --> 00:17:17,500
Yeah, we're close.

207
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:20,900
When you talk about him,

208
00:17:22,670 --> 00:17:24,700
you get this look in your eyes.

209
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:28,440
Oh.

210
00:17:29,690 --> 00:17:30,800
It's nothing.

211
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:38,300
I'm not trying to tease you.

212
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:41,900
I just see myself in you.

213
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:47,480
I once looked at someone that way too.

214
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:59,400
What did you do?

215
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,400
I thought

216
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,400
one day I'd be able to cut it out.

217
00:18:12,210 --> 00:18:13,300
Did you?

218
00:18:15,430 --> 00:18:17,400
I was young, you know.

219
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,600
In the end, I couldn't fight it.

220
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,400
So you left?

221
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:39,200
I blamed myself for a while.

222
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,090
I thought I should've been stronger.

223
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:54,300
But as I got older,

224
00:18:55,970 --> 00:18:58,100
I realized I'm only human.

225
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:08,000
It's…

226
00:19:10,070 --> 00:19:11,700
It's really hard, Auntie Lek.

227
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,800
That's just life.

228
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,700
But I've never hated myself.

229
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,300
Even now, I'm still proud

230
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:41,400
of the choice I made.

231
00:19:56,050 --> 00:19:58,400
Can I… hug you?

232
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,100
If you can't figure it out,

233
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:12,400
you don't have to right now.

234
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:24,400
Just be honest with your own feelings.

235
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,160
Okay?

236
00:20:35,330 --> 00:20:35,980
Okay.

237
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:37,840
And things will get better.

238
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,890
Auntie Lek seems

239
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,320
really happy with her life, doesn't she?

240
00:20:55,950 --> 00:20:58,900
When she talked about God,

241
00:20:59,950 --> 00:21:02,400
she didn't seem sad

242
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:04,000
or angry.

243
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,690
She looked really happy.

244
00:21:18,330 --> 00:21:20,000
Someday, you'll be like that too.

245
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:27,200
Someday…

246
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:37,200
do you think

247
00:21:39,930 --> 00:21:42,500
there's a place up there
for the two of us?

248
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:14,900
MARIA SAOWANEE SAWATDIRAKKUL

249
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:21,930
PAOLO PRACHA SAWATDIRAKKUL

250
00:22:24,470 --> 00:22:26,100
Everything is so hard.

251
00:22:27,350 --> 00:22:32,000
Mom, Dad, are you still waiting
for Rak in heaven?

252
00:22:41,350 --> 00:22:42,400
Who's Rak?

253
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,280
Mind your business.

254
00:22:53,870 --> 00:22:55,000
Tanrak's mom and dad,

255
00:22:56,310 --> 00:22:57,360
who's Rak?

256
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:04,100
When I was little,

257
00:23:05,070 --> 00:23:10,700
I called myself Rak with my parents.

258
00:23:13,950 --> 00:23:14,950
Really?

259
00:23:15,140 --> 00:23:16,300
Wow. Little Rak.

260
00:23:17,090 --> 00:23:18,200
Little Rak.

261
00:23:18,670 --> 00:23:20,500
Hey, don't push it.

262
00:23:21,450 --> 00:23:22,780
My parents are watching.

263
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:30,600
Try calling yourself Rak with me too.

264
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:33,800
What, are you my parent?

265
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:36,200
Why would I call myself Rak with you?

266
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,400
I'm not.

267
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:46,100
So how should I introduce myself
to your parents?

268
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:48,700
Your boyfriend?

269
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:51,120
Your lover?

270
00:23:52,460 --> 00:23:53,460
Your sweetheart?

271
00:23:55,190 --> 00:23:57,000
Or Rak's sweetheart?

272
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:02,810
"Rak's sweetheart” sounds cute,
doesn't it?

273
00:24:07,330 --> 00:24:08,800
Mom, Dad,

274
00:24:10,110 --> 00:24:11,110
this is…

275
00:24:12,050 --> 00:24:13,050
Barth.

276
00:24:14,410 --> 00:24:15,800
He's kind of a jerk.

277
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:19,990
Happy now?

278
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:26,830
Ahem.

279
00:24:27,930 --> 00:24:29,100
Tanrak's mom and dad,

280
00:24:30,410 --> 00:24:32,000
you don't have to worry from now on.

281
00:24:32,570 --> 00:24:34,040
I'll take care of Tanrak.

282
00:24:37,490 --> 00:24:39,200
You? Take care of me?

283
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,700
I'm the one who has to take care of you.

284
00:24:42,810 --> 00:24:44,500
You can barely handle your own life.

285
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:47,500
Hurry up. Help me with this.

286
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:51,600
I can take care of you, Rak.

287
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:54,560
Really?

288
00:24:55,730 --> 00:24:58,500
You even make me do your homework.

289
00:25:02,590 --> 00:25:04,030
I bring you along when I skip class.

290
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:12,200
Come on, help me.

291
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:14,400
I'm helping Rak.

292
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:28,780
Auntie Lek, we have to go now.

293
00:25:30,580 --> 00:25:31,580
Wait a second.

294
00:25:40,170 --> 00:25:41,400
This is my number.

295
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:43,420
Come visit again when you have time.

296
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:45,620
I will.

297
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:48,200
And this Bible

298
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:52,370
belonged to your dad.
I borrowed it from him.

299
00:25:56,190 --> 00:25:58,000
It should be with you.

300
00:25:58,050 --> 00:25:59,490
PAOLO PRACHA SAWATDIRAKKUL

301
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:03,400
Thank you, Auntie Lek.

302
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,700
Thank you so much.

303
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:07,400
I pray

304
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:09,700
that God watches over you both.

305
00:26:13,830 --> 00:26:14,830
Thank you.

306
00:26:19,180 --> 00:26:20,300
Don't forget,

307
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:23,700
you can love God

308
00:26:24,930 --> 00:26:26,930
and love yourself at the same time.

309
00:26:37,810 --> 00:26:38,450
Goodbye.

310
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:39,730
Goodbye.

311
00:26:40,190 --> 00:26:41,350
Have a safe trip.

312
00:26:41,940 --> 00:26:42,940
Yes.

313
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:52,780
♪ I've heard people say,
there's a place somewhere ♪

314
00:26:53,090 --> 00:26:56,600
♪ A land like a beautiful dream
beyond compare ♪

315
00:26:56,730 --> 00:26:59,980
♪ Where every soul lives endlessly ♪

316
00:27:01,130 --> 00:27:04,900
♪ I used to dream one day
that's where I'd be ♪

317
00:27:06,140 --> 00:27:14,100
♪ But since the day I found you,
a brand-new world opened up for me ♪

318
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:19,170
♪ With you right here,
with us right here ♪

319
00:27:19,430 --> 00:27:22,900
♪ There's nowhere else I'd rather be ♪

320
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:27,480
♪ Every second ♪
♪ From that moment ♪

321
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:29,763
♪ That I have you near ♪

322
00:27:29,782 --> 00:27:33,730
♪ Feels like I've found
the land of my dreams ♪

323
00:27:34,230 --> 00:27:39,400
♪ My world turns so beautiful
I wanna stop the time ♪

324
00:27:39,580 --> 00:27:42,800
♪ And hold this moment
for as long as I can ♪

325
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:45,183
♪ If heaven is real ♪
♪ If it's not real ♪

326
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:47,299
♪ how beautiful could it be ♪

327
00:27:47,610 --> 00:27:51,800
♪ I'm not so sure if I need to see ♪

328
00:27:52,140 --> 00:27:56,900
♪ As long as you're the one here
standing next to me ♪

329
00:27:56,930 --> 00:28:02,490
♪ If heaven doesn't have you there,
that's not where I wanna be ♪

330
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:06,400
I too have someone important
I want you to meet.

331
00:28:13,180 --> 00:28:14,380
Is your mom strict?

332
00:28:15,350 --> 00:28:18,810
What should I call her?

333
00:28:19,250 --> 00:28:21,200
Should I call her Auntie?

334
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,180
Or just Barth's mom?

335
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:27,580
Call her whatever.

336
00:28:28,140 --> 00:28:29,140
My mom's nice.

337
00:28:30,260 --> 00:28:31,800
Once she sees you're Christian,

338
00:28:32,410 --> 00:28:33,410
you'll be fine.

339
00:28:48,050 --> 00:28:49,100
What?

340
00:28:51,220 --> 00:28:54,700
Relatives of Ms. Busaya Tungwongwat,
you may see the inmate now.

341
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:57,420
Let's go.

342
00:29:30,070 --> 00:29:31,070
Barth.

343
00:29:35,170 --> 00:29:36,500
Is school out already?

344
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:38,300
Or did you take a day off?

345
00:29:39,410 --> 00:29:41,400
It's Founder's Day, Mom.

346
00:29:42,230 --> 00:29:44,600
The school brought us to Bangkok
on a field trip,

347
00:29:44,770 --> 00:29:46,200
so I asked to stop by and see you.

348
00:29:57,510 --> 00:29:58,900
Are you sick?

349
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:02,680
There's a flu outbreak in here.

350
00:30:02,710 --> 00:30:04,100
Is it spreading outside?

351
00:30:08,190 --> 00:30:09,400
I'm not sick, Mom.

352
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,700
It's just dusty.

353
00:30:12,510 --> 00:30:13,510
My nose hurts.

354
00:30:15,830 --> 00:30:18,400
Then rinse your nose with saline.

355
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:20,300
Remember how I taught you?

356
00:30:22,150 --> 00:30:22,810
I know.

357
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:24,200
I remember, Mom.

358
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,100
Oh.

359
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:31,370
Come here.

360
00:30:32,060 --> 00:30:33,600
This is Tanrak.

361
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:36,160
He's my friend from school.

362
00:30:37,470 --> 00:30:40,900
We came here together,
so I brought him to meet you.

363
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,600
Hello.

364
00:30:44,990 --> 00:30:46,900
What a beautiful name. Tanrak.

365
00:30:48,650 --> 00:30:49,850
Did you just transfer there?

366
00:30:49,940 --> 00:30:51,200
You look unfamiliar.

367
00:30:58,720 --> 00:30:59,720
Yes.

368
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:01,860
Barth's mom.

369
00:31:03,340 --> 00:31:05,000
Just call me Mom.

370
00:31:09,990 --> 00:31:11,700
You're Catholic too?

371
00:31:12,420 --> 00:31:13,450
That's wonderful.

372
00:31:14,820 --> 00:31:16,780
Do you get to pray at school?

373
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:21,000
Mom, what are you talking about now?

374
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:26,400
Please look after Barth for me.

375
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:30,000
With me in here, he must be lonely.

376
00:31:34,050 --> 00:31:35,700
He doesn't have many friends either.

377
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,520
When Barth went to school,

378
00:31:39,940 --> 00:31:42,800
he always came back and told me
everything that happened.

379
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:46,600
Bad food, he'd complain.

380
00:31:47,460 --> 00:31:48,800
Strict teachers, he'd complain.

381
00:31:53,820 --> 00:31:54,900
It's a shame.

382
00:32:00,170 --> 00:32:03,600
Tanrak,
listen to him complain for me, okay?

383
00:32:13,290 --> 00:32:14,700
Help each other study.

384
00:32:16,990 --> 00:32:18,600
Do you still stay up late?

385
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:22,350
Mom, that was when I was little.

386
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:24,200
I'm a grown-up now.

387
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:25,970
I'm in Grade 12.

388
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,200
Soon enough, I'll graduate.
Then I can work.

389
00:32:31,630 --> 00:32:34,000
You talk like I'm still a kid.

390
00:32:35,870 --> 00:32:37,000
Still nagging like always.

391
00:32:40,950 --> 00:32:42,800
You've always said you were grown up.

392
00:32:45,390 --> 00:32:47,900
You said the same thing when you were ten.

393
00:32:53,630 --> 00:32:55,180
You know how happy I am

394
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:57,570
that you came to see me?

395
00:33:00,350 --> 00:33:01,800
Next time you have a day off,

396
00:33:02,410 --> 00:33:04,000
will you come again?

397
00:33:11,620 --> 00:33:12,620
I'm gonna go.

398
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:17,360
Goodbye, Mom.

399
00:33:27,210 --> 00:33:29,500
Lawyer Kai came to see me the other day.

400
00:33:29,980 --> 00:33:33,000
He said the police found more evidence.

401
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,400
What evidence?

402
00:33:38,870 --> 00:33:41,100
They dug up old incidents.

403
00:33:42,630 --> 00:33:46,200
Like that time he put me in the hospital.

404
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:47,840
Remember?

405
00:33:50,350 --> 00:33:51,400
Actually,

406
00:33:52,380 --> 00:33:54,600
I should be the one in there,

407
00:33:56,350 --> 00:33:57,350
not you.

408
00:34:01,990 --> 00:34:04,200
If that happened,
how could I live with myself?

409
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:11,000
Let me do my job as your mother.

410
00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:19,300
Uncle Kai said this time,

411
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:25,300
the court may be sympathetic.

412
00:34:27,860 --> 00:34:30,100
I might be cleared of the charges.

413
00:34:30,870 --> 00:34:32,000
Or at least,

414
00:34:33,150 --> 00:34:36,100
I may have less than a year left.

415
00:34:41,060 --> 00:34:42,800
Pray for me, Barth.

416
00:34:45,620 --> 00:34:46,700
I'll hang in there.

417
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,380
You have to hang in there too.

418
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:56,480
I'll…

419
00:34:58,230 --> 00:34:59,700
pray for you.

420
00:35:08,370 --> 00:35:10,300
When I get out, I'll hug you.

421
00:35:13,780 --> 00:35:15,100
I love you.

422
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:23,620
Do you…

423
00:35:24,910 --> 00:35:26,900
love me more than your God?

424
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:33,900
More.

425
00:35:35,820 --> 00:35:37,100
More than anything.

426
00:35:38,050 --> 00:35:39,800
More than my own life.

427
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:17,300
I love you, Mom.

428
00:36:51,090 --> 00:36:52,090
Barth.

429
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:54,400
Let me use the bathroom real quick.

430
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:56,380
Okay.

431
00:39:53,690 --> 00:39:55,180
College life looks fun?

432
00:39:55,330 --> 00:39:56,330
Don't you think?

433
00:39:58,820 --> 00:39:59,820
Yeah.

434
00:40:01,410 --> 00:40:04,400
Just thinking about it is fun, isn't it?

435
00:40:07,580 --> 00:40:08,580
Yeah.

436
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:11,200
But I think

437
00:40:12,830 --> 00:40:14,300
college isn't for me.

438
00:40:16,780 --> 00:40:18,700
I probably couldn't even pass
the entrance exam.

439
00:40:19,180 --> 00:40:20,700
And even if I did,

440
00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:24,700
I wouldn't have money for tuition anyway.

441
00:40:25,530 --> 00:40:27,200
Plus food and rent.

442
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:32,700
But if I could,
I'd probably go to trade school,

443
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:35,000
study for a year,

444
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:39,100
then get a job and make some money.

445
00:40:44,290 --> 00:40:45,290
What about you?

446
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:47,200
What do you want to study?

447
00:40:53,850 --> 00:40:54,850
I…

448
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:56,700
I really don't know.

449
00:40:57,330 --> 00:40:59,010
I mean, I honestly have no idea.

450
00:41:00,500 --> 00:41:03,200
If I try to picture anything else,
I can't see it at all.

451
00:41:04,100 --> 00:41:07,100
I grew up at Magdalene House.

452
00:41:08,110 --> 00:41:09,800
If I had to choose another path,

453
00:41:10,590 --> 00:41:11,900
I don't think I'd know how.

454
00:41:16,490 --> 00:41:17,490
Yeah.

455
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:40,290
KANCHANABURI NONG PRUE

456
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:45,900
Two for the 7 p.m. bus, please.

457
00:41:46,230 --> 00:41:48,400
Oh, the 7 p.m. bus is full.

458
00:41:50,900 --> 00:41:55,600
The earliest would be tomorrow at 6 a.m.

459
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:58,500
What now?

460
00:41:58,570 --> 00:41:59,800
It's not until 6 tomorrow.

461
00:42:01,530 --> 00:42:03,600
We'll have to find somewhere
to sleep tonight.

462
00:42:05,430 --> 00:42:06,430
Come on.

463
00:42:14,030 --> 00:42:15,030
Hey, boys.

464
00:42:16,850 --> 00:42:19,170
There's a cheap motel
in the alley over there.

465
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:22,100
But the vibe's a little weird.

466
00:43:02,050 --> 00:43:03,050
Oh!

467
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:08,880
Hey!

468
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:35,850
I think it's okay.

469
00:43:37,270 --> 00:43:38,400
It's only 300 baht.

470
00:43:51,670 --> 00:43:53,300
I'm gonna go buy something.

471
00:43:54,220 --> 00:43:55,220
You want anything?

472
00:44:11,510 --> 00:44:12,700
Try it if you want.

473
00:44:15,090 --> 00:44:16,600
One puff won't kill you.

474
00:44:42,590 --> 00:44:44,100
What's so great about this?

475
00:44:44,800 --> 00:44:46,600
Why do people like smoking so much?

476
00:44:49,380 --> 00:44:51,300
My dad said it helps with stress.

477
00:44:52,340 --> 00:44:55,000
Like, when you smoke,
your mind goes blank or something.

478
00:44:55,090 --> 00:44:56,090
Yeah.

479
00:44:56,440 --> 00:44:57,440
You try it.

480
00:44:57,820 --> 00:44:59,000
Maybe you'll feel lighter.

481
00:45:13,340 --> 00:45:14,340
There.

482
00:45:14,550 --> 00:45:15,550
Feel lighter?

483
00:45:16,610 --> 00:45:17,770
More stressed than before.

484
00:45:23,980 --> 00:45:25,180
Screw it.

485
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:39,480
I don't want tomorrow to come.

486
00:45:41,350 --> 00:45:42,350
Yeah.

487
00:45:42,630 --> 00:45:43,700
Me neither.

488
00:45:48,080 --> 00:45:50,500
So what are you gonna do next?

489
00:45:56,090 --> 00:45:57,200
I still don't know.

490
00:46:25,180 --> 00:46:30,700
♪ Amidst the rainfall ♪

491
00:46:32,090 --> 00:46:37,670
♪ This lonely heart of mine
comes back to life ♪

492
00:46:38,820 --> 00:46:44,500
♪ All the things I never held dear ♪

493
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:49,410
BARTH

494
00:46:51,310 --> 00:46:54,080
♪ The stars had never shone for me ♪

495
00:46:54,110 --> 00:46:57,200
♪ No beauty in their light ♪

496
00:46:58,030 --> 00:47:00,120
♪ For the first time, they bloomed ♪

497
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:04,600
♪ When I met you, they came alive ♪

498
00:47:05,010 --> 00:47:11,170
♪ The same old world feels new again ♪

499
00:47:11,520 --> 00:47:17,100
♪ Today you help me understand ♪

500
00:47:17,850 --> 00:47:20,300
♪ Every melody of a love song ♪

501
00:47:20,320 --> 00:47:22,230
♪ Playing in my heart ♪

502
00:47:22,260 --> 00:47:25,500
♪ Would never sound so beautiful ♪

503
00:47:25,640 --> 00:47:31,450
♪ Without you, next to me, never apart ♪

504
00:47:31,660 --> 00:47:34,140
♪ This song belongs to you and me ♪

505
00:47:34,170 --> 00:47:35,800
♪ To us only ♪

506
00:47:35,830 --> 00:47:38,080
♪ The sound inside has changed ♪

507
00:47:38,100 --> 00:47:40,300
♪ It will never be the same ♪

508
00:47:40,590 --> 00:47:41,960
♪ Because you ♪

509
00:47:42,300 --> 00:47:43,670
♪ Because you ♪

510
00:47:43,890 --> 00:47:47,990
♪ Fill my heart with the sound of love ♪

511
00:47:51,380 --> 00:47:57,900
♪ Fill my heart with the sound of love ♪

512
00:47:57,920 --> 00:47:59,370
PARADISE

513
00:48:02,580 --> 00:48:03,580
Are you asleep?

514
00:48:07,750 --> 00:48:08,750
Yeah.

515
00:48:14,120 --> 00:48:15,500
Then how are you answering me?

516
00:48:19,530 --> 00:48:20,700
Are you teasing me?

517
00:48:21,420 --> 00:48:22,420
Hm?

518
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:34,700
Well, you were acting all serious
when we first came in.

519
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:39,080
Barth.

520
00:48:41,950 --> 00:48:43,100
I'm going to sleep.

521
00:48:52,690 --> 00:48:54,410
I was just scared you'd change your mind.

522
00:48:59,380 --> 00:49:00,400
Are you sure?

523
00:49:05,050 --> 00:49:06,050
What about you?

524
00:49:11,690 --> 00:49:12,690
Yeah.

525
00:49:24,950 --> 00:49:25,950
Tanrak.

526
00:49:27,360 --> 00:49:28,360
What's wrong?

527
00:49:28,860 --> 00:49:30,000
What? Are you shy?

528
00:49:31,500 --> 00:49:32,500
Hm.

529
00:49:32,550 --> 00:49:33,690
- You're shy?
- Hm.

530
00:49:33,950 --> 00:49:35,100
What are you doing? Huh?

531
00:49:50,450 --> 00:49:51,470
I…

532
00:49:53,030 --> 00:49:54,400
I love you, Tanrak.

533
00:49:56,690 --> 00:49:58,100
I love you too.

534
00:53:15,020 --> 00:53:16,020
Tanrak.

535
00:53:40,750 --> 00:53:42,400
It took so long to get here.

536
00:53:45,270 --> 00:53:47,300
If the calling wasn't strong enough,

537
00:53:48,100 --> 00:53:49,640
he wouldn't have made it this far.

538
00:53:53,780 --> 00:53:54,780
That's true.

539
00:53:57,020 --> 00:53:58,400
It really has been a long time.

540
00:54:00,880 --> 00:54:03,400
Talking about it makes me miss those days.

541
00:54:05,430 --> 00:54:06,430
But…

542
00:54:06,590 --> 00:54:08,600
we can't go back and change anything now.

543
00:54:19,780 --> 00:54:20,780
Father.

544
00:54:25,960 --> 00:54:27,250
Feel free to look around, Barth.

545
00:54:27,310 --> 00:54:28,400
We'll talk later.

546
00:54:28,810 --> 00:54:29,810
Okay.

547
00:54:44,530 --> 00:54:46,010
All right, that should do it.

548
00:54:46,330 --> 00:54:48,800
Go pack up. The ceremony's about to start.

549
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:50,320
Go on.

550
00:54:52,550 --> 00:54:53,900
- Hello, Master Phak.
- Barth!

551
00:54:56,010 --> 00:54:57,610
I guess I can't call you Master anymore.

552
00:54:58,130 --> 00:54:59,300
Hello, Father Phak.

553
00:55:01,060 --> 00:55:02,300
You can just call me Phak.

554
00:55:02,760 --> 00:55:03,760
I don't mind.

555
00:55:05,740 --> 00:55:06,830
Better not.

556
00:55:07,590 --> 00:55:08,800
You're a priest now.

557
00:55:08,940 --> 00:55:10,090
It wouldn't be proper.

558
00:55:13,690 --> 00:55:15,580
But he's really steadfast, isn't he?

559
00:55:16,780 --> 00:55:20,100
Out of our whole class,
he's the only one left.

560
00:55:22,230 --> 00:55:23,800
Not "only one left.”

561
00:55:24,710 --> 00:55:26,380
One person made it all the way.

562
00:55:27,660 --> 00:55:29,800
It's been a long road to get here.

563
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:33,580
Those who left along the way
did nothing wrong.

564
00:55:48,290 --> 00:55:49,700
They really did nothing wrong?

565
00:55:58,140 --> 00:56:00,300
There's no such thing
as the "right” life, Barth.

566
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:05,000
Every life has its own path.

567
00:56:06,420 --> 00:56:08,530
God always gives us the chance to choose.

568
00:56:09,430 --> 00:56:11,500
As long as we remain in His love.

569
00:56:15,860 --> 00:56:18,640
So how have you two been?

570
00:56:49,040 --> 00:56:50,040
Father.

571
00:56:55,990 --> 00:56:57,580
I have something to confess.

572
00:57:04,310 --> 00:57:06,500
What would you like to confess, my child?

573
00:57:26,430 --> 00:57:27,700
I've sinned.

574
00:57:33,810 --> 00:57:35,500
I wronged the people who helped me.

575
00:57:40,500 --> 00:57:41,900
I sinned against God.

576
00:57:45,310 --> 00:57:46,800
I betrayed everyone

577
00:57:48,670 --> 00:57:50,100
who trusted me.

578
00:57:53,250 --> 00:57:54,600
Everyone

579
00:57:56,600 --> 00:57:58,300
who gave me a chance.

580
00:58:02,130 --> 00:58:03,130
Father.

581
00:58:06,900 --> 00:58:08,100
I'm scared.

582
00:58:14,030 --> 00:58:15,880
I'm scared I won't go to heaven.

583
00:58:19,490 --> 00:58:20,490
I'm scared.

584
00:58:22,700 --> 00:58:24,500
I won't get to see Him anymore.

585
00:58:30,740 --> 00:58:32,400
Don't worry, my child.

586
00:58:33,570 --> 00:58:35,900
God always gives you another chance.

587
00:58:37,290 --> 00:58:39,650
As long as you're truly sorry,

588
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:41,300
that's enough.

589
00:58:43,440 --> 00:58:44,550
God

590
00:58:45,860 --> 00:58:47,980
is still waiting for you in heaven.

591
00:58:49,230 --> 00:58:50,900
Your parents

592
00:58:52,430 --> 00:58:54,500
are still waiting for you there too.

593
00:59:00,280 --> 00:59:01,280
Father.

594
00:59:04,960 --> 00:59:06,300
You know it's me.

595
00:59:10,200 --> 00:59:11,900
Don't worry, my child.

596
00:59:13,130 --> 00:59:15,400
Even if you're not ordained,

597
00:59:16,390 --> 00:59:17,700
God

598
00:59:18,800 --> 00:59:21,400
can still live in your heart.

599
00:59:28,940 --> 00:59:32,700
He will remain there

600
00:59:33,900 --> 00:59:35,700
with you forever.

601
00:59:49,610 --> 00:59:50,700
It's okay.

602
00:59:51,550 --> 00:59:52,550
Tanrak.

603
00:59:58,140 --> 00:59:59,140
It's okay.

604
01:00:18,570 --> 01:00:19,570
It's okay.

605
01:00:28,470 --> 01:00:29,470
Father.

606
01:00:30,200 --> 01:00:31,230
I'm sorry.

607
01:00:32,810 --> 01:00:34,600
I feel so selfish.

608
01:00:37,460 --> 01:00:38,600
It's okay.

609
01:00:39,870 --> 01:00:41,370
It's okay, Tanrak.

610
01:00:44,830 --> 01:00:46,900
You need to forgive yourself.

611
01:00:48,210 --> 01:00:52,100
You've carried this long enough.

612
01:00:56,440 --> 01:00:59,480
You don't have to carry it
for the rest of your life.

613
01:02:34,190 --> 01:02:35,870
Back when I was still a student,

614
01:02:36,690 --> 01:02:39,670
many things taught me

615
01:02:40,780 --> 01:02:42,000
about the good things,

616
01:02:42,470 --> 01:02:43,700
the disappointments,

617
01:02:44,290 --> 01:02:45,400
the failures,

618
01:02:46,040 --> 01:02:47,040
love,

619
01:02:48,010 --> 01:02:49,400
and friendship.

620
01:02:50,730 --> 01:02:53,300
And three things always remain.

621
01:02:54,320 --> 01:02:55,320
Those are

622
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:57,000
faith,

623
01:02:58,360 --> 01:02:59,400
hope,

624
01:03:00,860 --> 01:03:01,910
and love.

625
01:03:09,570 --> 01:03:10,790
And love

626
01:03:11,690 --> 01:03:13,000
is the greatest of all.

627
01:03:41,570 --> 01:03:42,570
Tanrak.

628
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:45,900
I just ran into Father Phak.

629
01:03:47,150 --> 01:03:48,500
He asked about us.

630
01:03:50,720 --> 01:03:51,720
Really?

631
01:03:53,330 --> 01:03:54,600
What did you tell him?

632
01:03:58,600 --> 01:03:59,800
I told him,

633
01:04:02,100 --> 01:04:03,400
"I put him through a lot."

634
01:04:06,600 --> 01:04:09,250
We had to work for years
before we could go to college.

635
01:04:11,260 --> 01:04:12,300
Studying,

636
01:04:13,180 --> 01:04:14,380
working,

637
01:04:17,160 --> 01:04:18,500
trying to pay tuition.

638
01:04:21,700 --> 01:04:22,780
It wasn't easy.

639
01:04:25,170 --> 01:04:26,380
But…

640
01:04:29,470 --> 01:04:30,470
But what?

641
01:04:41,370 --> 01:04:43,150
But we never let go of each other

642
01:04:45,010 --> 01:04:46,700
from that day until now.

643
01:04:53,230 --> 01:04:54,230
Well,

644
01:04:55,570 --> 01:04:57,100
I tried to shake you off.

645
01:04:58,640 --> 01:05:00,200
But you just wouldn't come loose.

646
01:05:06,160 --> 01:05:07,800
Who was it that told me this?

647
01:05:10,070 --> 01:05:11,500
"No matter where I am,

648
01:05:13,020 --> 01:05:15,200
as long as you're next to me,
everything's fine."

649
01:05:31,610 --> 01:05:34,000
Do you remember
how I used to tease you all the time?

650
01:05:35,320 --> 01:05:36,320
I'd say,

651
01:05:37,730 --> 01:05:39,370
"Do you really believe in God?”

652
01:05:42,550 --> 01:05:43,550
Of course I remember.

653
01:05:43,800 --> 01:05:45,000
How could I not?

654
01:05:45,510 --> 01:05:47,100
You teased me every day.

655
01:05:53,690 --> 01:05:55,100
Back then, I thought

656
01:05:59,000 --> 01:06:00,300
if God was real,

657
01:06:03,320 --> 01:06:05,100
He probably didn't care much about me.

658
01:06:09,220 --> 01:06:11,300
But thinking about it now,

659
01:06:15,080 --> 01:06:16,200
I feel like

660
01:06:17,600 --> 01:06:19,100
no matter what I did,

661
01:06:21,840 --> 01:06:23,980
He never disappeared from my life.

662
01:06:28,130 --> 01:06:29,300
Without Him,

663
01:06:32,240 --> 01:06:33,580
I wouldn't have met you.

664
01:06:36,090 --> 01:06:37,600
And we wouldn't have today.

665
01:06:39,530 --> 01:06:40,530
Well, I…

666
01:06:42,050 --> 01:06:43,300
I used to think

667
01:06:44,250 --> 01:06:45,580
after meeting you,

668
01:06:46,300 --> 01:06:47,300
I had to choose.

669
01:06:48,860 --> 01:06:49,900
But actually,

670
01:06:50,670 --> 01:06:51,930
I never had to choose at all.

671
01:06:58,470 --> 01:07:01,800
Because ever since you came into my life,

672
01:07:03,250 --> 01:07:05,200
I never forgot God either.

673
01:07:37,600 --> 01:07:39,120
EUCHARISTIC CELEBRATION
AND PRIESTLY ORDINATION

674
01:07:39,140 --> 01:07:40,380
DEACON JOSEPH KONGDECH SAENKHAM

675
01:07:47,040 --> 01:07:48,040
Ahem.

676
01:07:49,500 --> 01:07:51,300
Hello, Father Kongdech.

677
01:07:54,670 --> 01:07:55,670
Are you messing with me?

678
01:07:57,930 --> 01:07:59,600
Just call me Kongdech like before.

679
01:08:00,350 --> 01:08:01,670
We're still friends.

680
01:08:02,430 --> 01:08:04,300
Just maybe skip the rude pronouns.

681
01:08:06,500 --> 01:08:10,400
I just wanted to say

682
01:08:10,950 --> 01:08:13,290
thank you for remembering my first sermon.

683
01:08:14,330 --> 01:08:15,330
Of course I remember.

684
01:08:16,920 --> 01:08:18,300
I don't have many friends.

685
01:08:18,640 --> 01:08:20,000
So whatever anyone says,

686
01:08:20,380 --> 01:08:21,580
I remember it all.

687
01:08:25,880 --> 01:08:29,570
Thank you so much, dear Father,
for still calling me your friend.

688
01:08:32,690 --> 01:08:34,000
Want to talk like old times?

689
01:08:34,580 --> 01:08:35,700
Might make you less nervous.

690
01:08:35,810 --> 01:08:39,400
You're so tense it's painful to watch.

691
01:08:39,540 --> 01:08:40,240
Okay, okay.

692
01:08:40,280 --> 01:08:41,670
What? Are you crazy?

693
01:08:41,760 --> 01:08:43,360
You can't talk to a priest like that.

694
01:08:44,250 --> 01:08:45,450
That's hell-worthy.

695
01:08:47,710 --> 01:08:48,710
Barth.

696
01:08:51,490 --> 01:08:52,650
Look at his robe.

697
01:08:54,410 --> 01:08:55,410
Father.

698
01:08:56,770 --> 01:08:58,500
Sorry, there's something on you.

699
01:08:59,650 --> 01:09:00,650
What is it?

700
01:09:01,590 --> 01:09:04,200
Oh, gray hair.

701
01:09:06,460 --> 01:09:07,460
You're old now.

702
01:09:09,880 --> 01:09:10,880
Yes, my child.

703
01:09:11,560 --> 01:09:12,690
Hell is hot, you know.

704
01:09:13,150 --> 01:09:15,900
Don't forget to bring cooling powder
when you fall in.

705
01:09:37,620 --> 01:09:40,300
I'm happy for you, man.

706
01:09:42,050 --> 01:09:43,050
Oops.

707
01:09:43,780 --> 01:09:46,700
I'm happy for you, Father Kongdech.

708
01:09:48,240 --> 01:09:51,200
Thank you, my child Tanrak.

709
01:09:53,830 --> 01:09:55,450
Please hear my confession too.

710
01:09:56,090 --> 01:09:57,800
I'll book you a month in advance.

711
01:09:58,190 --> 01:10:00,190
I have a feeling
you have a lot of sins to confess.

712
01:10:00,310 --> 01:10:01,310
My child, Barth.

713
01:10:10,020 --> 01:10:11,020
Father.

714
01:10:11,190 --> 01:10:13,870
I'm sorry, and thank you again
for everything.

715
01:10:15,870 --> 01:10:17,400
Love yourself more.

716
01:10:18,010 --> 01:10:20,520
And if you get the chance,
come back and visit me sometime.

717
01:10:59,710 --> 01:11:00,710
Hey, Tan.

718
01:11:02,910 --> 01:11:04,000
If we get ordained,

719
01:11:04,830 --> 01:11:07,500
what would your first sermon be about?

720
01:11:11,030 --> 01:11:12,400
I want to preach about

721
01:11:12,760 --> 01:11:17,100
love, faith, and hope from Corinthians.

722
01:11:18,380 --> 01:11:19,100
Why?

723
01:11:19,177 --> 01:11:24,300
♪ Turn into memories I treasure for life ♪

724
01:11:24,707 --> 01:11:27,432
♪ The stars had never shone for me ♪

725
01:11:27,470 --> 01:11:30,530
♪ No beauty in their light ♪

726
01:11:31,396 --> 01:11:33,500
♪ For the first time, they bloomed ♪

727
01:11:33,520 --> 01:11:37,692
♪ When I met you, they came alive ♪

728
01:11:38,381 --> 01:11:44,600
♪ The same old world feels new again ♪

729
01:11:44,902 --> 01:11:50,384
♪ Today you help me understand ♪

730
01:11:51,248 --> 01:11:53,630
♪ Every melody of a love song ♪

731
01:11:53,651 --> 01:11:55,399
♪ Playing in my heart ♪

732
01:11:55,520 --> 01:11:58,500
Humans can live without faith.

733
01:12:00,360 --> 01:12:02,600
Humans can live without hope.

734
01:12:03,940 --> 01:12:07,400
But humans cannot live without love.

735
01:12:09,540 --> 01:12:11,100
Even without faith,

736
01:12:11,720 --> 01:12:13,670
if humans love deeply enough,

737
01:12:14,170 --> 01:12:15,490
they will believe.

738
01:12:20,550 --> 01:12:22,000
Even without hope,

739
01:12:22,680 --> 01:12:24,730
if humans love deeply enough,

740
01:12:25,570 --> 01:12:26,900
they will hope.

741
01:12:28,400 --> 01:12:30,500
But without love,

742
01:12:31,130 --> 01:12:34,150
humans have no chance of finding Him.

743
01:12:37,130 --> 01:12:40,600
God's love is everything.

744
01:12:41,910 --> 01:12:43,530
It is love for oneself.

745
01:12:44,450 --> 01:12:46,500
It is love for one's neighbor.

746
01:12:51,740 --> 01:12:55,500
For He created all things.

747
01:12:57,350 --> 01:12:58,600
Wherever there is love,

748
01:12:59,290 --> 01:13:02,100
He is always present there.

749
01:13:05,430 --> 01:13:07,810
Love is therefore the most important

750
01:13:08,580 --> 01:13:10,000
and the greatest of all.

751
01:13:12,830 --> 01:13:16,400
Because love is never without Him.

752
01:13:16,420 --> 01:13:17,420
THE END

753
01:13:17,461 --> 01:13:20,495
♪ The same old world feels new again ♪

754
01:13:20,928 --> 01:13:26,383
♪ Today you help me understand ♪

755
01:13:27,219 --> 01:13:29,628
♪ Every melody of a love song ♪

756
01:13:29,650 --> 01:13:31,410
♪ Playing in my heart ♪

757
01:13:31,586 --> 01:13:34,900
♪ Would never sound so beautiful ♪

758
01:13:34,993 --> 01:13:40,781
♪ Without you, next to me, never apart ♪

759
01:13:41,018 --> 01:13:43,462
♪ This song belongs to you and me ♪

760
01:13:43,536 --> 01:13:45,165
♪ To us only ♪

761
01:13:45,210 --> 01:13:47,424
♪ The sound inside has changed ♪

762
01:13:47,440 --> 01:13:49,628
♪ It will never be the same ♪

763
01:13:50,030 --> 01:13:51,300
♪ Because you ♪

764
01:13:51,700 --> 01:13:53,062
♪ Because you ♪

765
01:13:53,250 --> 01:13:58,101
♪ Fill my heart with the sound of love ♪

766
01:14:00,739 --> 01:14:07,183
♪ Fill my heart with the sound of love ♪

767
01:14:30,770 --> 01:14:31,900
Took you long enough.

768
01:14:33,470 --> 01:14:34,500
Tired today?

769
01:14:36,010 --> 01:14:37,700
Two of my staff quit today.

770
01:14:38,850 --> 01:14:39,970
Way more tiring than usual.

771
01:14:43,810 --> 01:14:44,950
I'm sore all over.

772
01:14:47,690 --> 01:14:48,690
Hold onto this for me.

773
01:14:51,820 --> 01:14:52,820
Barth.

774
01:14:54,170 --> 01:14:56,130
Why are you getting into bed
without showering?

775
01:14:56,150 --> 01:14:57,150
You stink.

776
01:14:57,360 --> 01:14:59,200
Let me lie down for a second. I'm tired.

777
01:15:00,270 --> 01:15:01,270
Please.

778
01:15:01,950 --> 01:15:03,200
So tired.

779
01:15:04,240 --> 01:15:04,950
Go shower.

780
01:15:04,970 --> 01:15:06,690
I'm really tired. Just a second.

781
01:15:07,140 --> 01:15:09,000
Just a second. Just a second.

782
01:15:11,490 --> 01:15:13,570
Hurry up and shower
before this becomes a habit.

783
01:15:20,270 --> 01:15:21,600
Still nagging like always.

784
01:15:27,550 --> 01:15:29,050
One minute, Rak.

785
01:15:30,580 --> 01:15:31,850
You stink.

786
01:15:49,060 --> 01:15:51,100
You must really like this necklace.

787
01:15:52,120 --> 01:15:53,170
You wear it every day.

788
01:15:57,430 --> 01:16:03,200
I went from being Mom's beloved

789
01:16:04,570 --> 01:16:05,800
to being…

790
01:16:06,240 --> 01:16:07,500
beloved by…

791
01:16:09,660 --> 01:16:10,660
By who?

792
01:16:13,810 --> 01:16:15,800
God.

793
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:27,000
Or you?

794
01:16:29,450 --> 01:16:31,100
Of course you're Barth's.

795
01:16:39,230 --> 01:16:40,230
You know,

796
01:16:40,630 --> 01:16:42,300
I used to think.

797
01:16:42,750 --> 01:16:44,290
God probably didn't love me much.

798
01:16:45,670 --> 01:16:46,670
Why?

799
01:16:49,360 --> 01:16:50,600
Look at my life back then.

800
01:16:50,960 --> 01:16:51,960
It was a total mess.

801
01:16:53,150 --> 01:16:55,700
It felt like He had forgotten me.

802
01:16:58,640 --> 01:17:01,840
But He sent you to meet me.

803
01:17:06,230 --> 01:17:08,210
Why does that sound like a punishment?

804
01:17:09,850 --> 01:17:10,850
It's not.

805
01:17:12,320 --> 01:17:13,500
To me,

806
01:17:14,500 --> 01:17:15,800
it's a miracle.

807
01:17:31,840 --> 01:17:36,300
You're Barth's one and only beloved.

808
01:17:42,340 --> 01:17:43,340
Aren't you?

809
01:18:03,180 --> 01:18:04,180
Am I?

810
01:18:08,530 --> 01:18:10,500
Now I've got the motivation to shower.

811
01:18:11,900 --> 01:18:13,700
I'm gonna shower. Be right back.

812
01:18:17,410 --> 01:18:18,410
Hey.

813
01:18:33,230 --> 01:18:37,180
Come back for more kisses
after your shower.

814
01:18:41,620 --> 01:18:42,850
I'll shower really fast.

815
01:18:58,490 --> 01:18:59,750
I don't wanna shower anymore.

816
01:19:00,490 --> 01:19:01,600
I wanna stay right here.

817
01:19:01,830 --> 01:19:03,800
Weren't you going to shower?

818
01:19:04,390 --> 01:19:05,700
Barth.

819
01:19:06,010 --> 01:19:06,900
One second.

820
01:19:07,020 --> 01:19:07,900
You stink.

821
01:19:07,920 --> 01:19:09,050
Let me lie here first.

822
01:19:09,070 --> 01:19:10,500
Go lie on your own side.

823
01:19:10,970 --> 01:19:11,970
Come here.

824
01:19:12,610 --> 01:19:13,610
Come on.

825
01:19:14,050 --> 01:19:15,100
Come with me.

826
01:19:15,370 --> 01:19:16,370
Hey, Barth.

827
01:19:16,830 --> 01:19:17,830
Barth.

828
01:19:18,570 --> 01:19:19,700
Just stay for a second.

829
01:19:21,050 --> 01:19:22,050
Just a second.

830
01:19:22,150 --> 01:19:23,150
Just a second.

831
01:19:25,990 --> 01:19:26,990
Come on.

832
01:19:36,090 --> 01:19:38,380
♪ Every second ♪
♪ From that moment ♪

833
01:19:38,400 --> 01:19:40,694
♪ That I have you near ♪

834
01:19:40,709 --> 01:19:44,800
♪ Feels like I've found
the land of my dreams ♪

835
01:19:45,130 --> 01:19:50,300
♪ My world turns so beautiful
I wanna stop the time ♪

836
01:19:50,320 --> 01:19:53,741
TAN…RAK

837
01:19:53,760 --> 01:19:56,110
♪ If heaven is real ♪
♪ If it's not real ♪

838
01:19:56,120 --> 01:19:58,300
♪ how beautiful could it be ♪

839
01:19:58,540 --> 01:20:02,600
♪ I'm not so sure if I need to see ♪

840
01:20:03,060 --> 01:20:07,730
♪ As long as you're the one here
standing next to me ♪

841
01:20:07,870 --> 01:20:14,800
♪ If heaven doesn't have you there,
that's not where I wanna be ♪

842
01:20:17,600 --> 01:20:24,800
TO EVERY KIND OF LOVE AND FAITH
